messages.message:
We know about this already for a while, though it keeps getting pushed down some quarters... Would be great to set up a short-track experiment! ^^

What I like the most is this:
> breakthrough came from the MUVERA paper. Instead of searching through all patch embeddings independently, MUVERA reduces multi-vector search to single-vector similarity using fixed-dimensional encodings. Think of it as creating a “summary fingerprint” that preserves the rich patch interactions while being orders of magnitude faster to search.
MUVERA: https://research.google/blog/muvera-making-multi-vector-retrieval-as-fast-as-single-vector-search/
